\f1\b0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3-4 pounds small Yukon gold potatoes\
{\listtext	\'95	}Salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}16 tablespoons (2 sticks) unsalted butter\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 yellow onion, roughly chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cloves garlic, roughly chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}Freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 cups heavy cream\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs50 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs48 \cf0 Place the potatoes in a large pot, cover with cold water and season with salt. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat to medium and simmer until tender. Drain well, then cool slightly. Return the potatoes to the pot and, using a masher, mash the potatoes.\
Meanwhile, melt the butter in medium, heavy skillet over medium heat. Add the onions and saute until translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and saute about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Add the cream and cook over medium-low heat for 3 minutes longer.\
Add cream mixture to the mashed potatoes and stir to combine until the liquid is fully absorbed. Season with salt and pepper. Serve immediately.\
